# Datadog OAuth credentials for the dashboard's Connect Datadog flow.
# Optional — the log drains wizard falls back to paste-token when these
# are unset, which is the easiest path for local-dev testing.
#
# To enable the OAuth path locally:
#   1. Register a Datadog OAuth client at
#      https://docs.datadoghq.com/developers/authorization/
#      with the redirect URI below pointing at your local dashboard.
#   2. Copy this file to dev/.env.datadog (no .example) and fill in the
#      values. The Tiltfile sources it automatically.
#
# DATADOG_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID=...
# DATADOG_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# DATADOG_OAUTH_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/integrations/datadog/callback
